[{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"root = pwd() |> dirname |> dirname |> dirname","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/#User's-guide","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/guide/#Converting-text-documents-to-a-citable-corpus","page":"User's guide","title":"Converting text documents to a citable corpus","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"The CitableTeiReaders package provides the readcitable function to read a source document and create a CitableTextCorpus (from the CitableCorpus package), citable by CtsUrn (from the CitableText package).  ","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"Three arguments are required, and a fourth is optional:","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"the document source. The document source is a string value, giving either a literal string of text to parse, a file name, or a URL.\nthe CTS URN identifying the document.\na subtype of the CiteStructureTrait.  This is a Julia type that understands how to parse the citation scheme of the document you want to read.\n(optional) a subtype of the ReaderType (from CitableBase).  This parameter may be omitted if the document source is a literal string value; use FileReader or UrlReader if the document source is a file name or URL, respectively.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/#An-XML-example","page":"User's guide","title":"An XML example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"You will always want to use these three packages from the CITE architecture:","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"using CitableTeiReaders\nusing CitableText, CitableBase","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"We'll work with a valid TEI file, aratea.xml, in the test/data directory of this repository, and define its URN.  These will be the first two parameters to readcitable.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"f = joinpath(root, \"test\", \"data\", \"aratea.xml\")\narateaurn = CtsUrn(\"urn:cts:latinLit:phi0881.phi003.bern88:\")","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"Since our document cites its passages by poetic line using the TEI l element, we will use the TEIPoeticLine type as our third parameter.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"One option is to read the source file into a string, and call readcitable with three arguments.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"cexsrc = read(f, String)\nstringcorpus = readcitable(cexsrc, arateaurn, TEIPoeticLine)","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"Alternatively, we can include a FileReader as the fourth argument, and read the corpus directly from the file. ","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"filecorpus = readcitable(f, arateaurn, TEIPoeticLine, FileReader)","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"The resulting corpora are identical.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"stringcorpus == filecorpus","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/#A-non-XML-example","page":"User's guide","title":"A non-XML example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"The readcitable is not limited to XML source documents: it will accept any pairing of source data with a subtype of CiteStructureTrait that can parse the source into a CitableTextCorpus. For example, the CitableTeiReaders packages includes a DelimitedText type that parses a delimited-text source in two columns.  The first column contains the CTS URN for the passage, and the second column its text contents.  ","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"Since the source already has computed URN values, we use nothing as the value of the document's URN.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"src = \"\"\"urn:cts:hmt:aristonicus.signs.eng:7|He (Aristarchus) took (over) the obelos from the edition of Zenodotus.\nurn:cts:hmt:aristonicus.signs.eng:8|And as he rejected lines from the poem, he placed it (the obelos) next to them, as if to corpses of humans.\nurn:cts:hmt:aristonicus.signs.eng:9|His (Aristarchus') rationale/reason for athetesis is two-fold.\n\"\"\"\naristonicus = readcitable(src, nothing, DelimitedText)","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/#Other-utilities","page":"User's guide","title":"Other utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"The package includes an ezxmlstring function to serialize nodes parsed with EzXML.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/guide/","page":"User's guide","title":"User's guide","text":"using CitableTeiReaders\nusing EzXML\nxml = \"<root><choice><abbr>Mr.</abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice> Big.</root>\"\nparsed = parsexml(xml)\nelem = findfirst(\"/root\", parsed.root)\nezxmlstring(elem)\n\n# output\n\n\"<root><choice><abbr>Mr.</abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice> Big.</root>\"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"root = pwd() |> dirname |> dirname","category":"page"},{"location":"#CitableTeiReaders.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"CitableTeiReaders.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Read documents in TEI XML and other formats into citable text objects.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"note: Note\nThe package name is misleading:  converting text documents into citable text objects is not limited to TEI-compliant XML or even to XML at all.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quick-example","page":"Home","title":"Quick example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the test/data directory of this repository, the file aratea.xml is a TEI document cited by poetic line (TEI l element within text/body).  We will start by using three packages to work with citable texts, and by defining the URN for the text to read.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using CitableTeiReaders\nusing CitableText, CitableBase\n\nf = joinpath(root, \"test\", \"data\", \"aratea.xml\")\narateaurn = CtsUrn(\"urn:cts:latinLit:phi0881.phi003.bern88:\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We can create a citable corpus with the readcitable function. ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"corpus = readcitable(f, arateaurn, TEIPoeticLine, FileReader)","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#API-documentation","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/#The-readcitable-function","page":"API documentation","title":"The readcitable function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"Use the readcitable function to create a citable corpus from a source document.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"readcitable","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.readcitable","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.readcitable","text":"Read from src  a citable document identified by urn. Its citation scheme must be parseable using the type citescheme.\n\nreadcitable(src, urn, citescheme)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRead from file fname  a citable document identified by urn. Its citation scheme must be parseable using the type citescheme.\n\nreadcitable(fname, urn, citescheme, rdr)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRead from url  a citable document identified by urn. Its citation scheme must be parseable using the type citescheme.\n\nreadcitable(url, urn, citescheme, rdr)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIPoeticLine.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIAnonblock.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIDivAb.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIDivLine.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIDivDivDiv.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type TEIThreeDivsGrouped.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplementation of readcitable for type DelimitedText.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Subtypes-of-CiteStructureTrait","page":"API documentation","title":"Subtypes of CiteStructureTrait","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"Any package can implement the CiteStructure with a custom type to supply to the readcitable function.  The following types are included in the CitableTeiReaders package.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#Delimited-text-file","page":"API documentation","title":"Delimited-text file","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"DelimitedText","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.DelimitedText","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.DelimitedText","text":"Singleton type for delimited-text document with citation scheme of arbitrary depth already expressed with URNs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#XML-cited-by-one-tier-citation-scheme","page":"API documentation","title":"XML cited by one-tier citation scheme","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"TEIPoeticLine\nTEIAnonblock","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIPoeticLine","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIPoeticLine","text":"Singleton type for TEI document cited by poetic line using TEI l.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIAnonblock","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIAnonblock","text":"Singleton type for TEI document cited by prose block using TEI ab.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#XML-cited-by-two-tier-citation-scheme","page":"API documentation","title":"XML cited by two-tier citation scheme","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"TEIDivAb\nTEIDivLine","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivAb","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivAb","text":"Singleton type for TEI document cited in two tiers using TEI div and ab elements.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivLine","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivLine","text":"Singleton type for TEI document cited in two tiers using TEI div and l.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#XML-cited-by-three-tier-citation-scheme","page":"API documentation","title":"XML cited by three-tier citation scheme","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"TEIDivDivDiv\nTEIThreeDivsGrouped","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivDivDiv","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIDivDivDiv","text":"Singleton type for TEI document cited in three tiers using TEI div, div and div.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.TEIThreeDivsGrouped","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.TEIThreeDivsGrouped","text":"Singleton type for grouped TEI documents cited in three tiers using TEI group, div and div.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#A-useful-utility-function","page":"API documentation","title":"A useful utility function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"ezxmlstring","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.ezxmlstring","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.ezxmlstring","text":"ezxmlstring(n)\n\n\nSerialize an EzXML.Node to an XML string. If a node n was created by parsing an XML string, the output of ezxmlstring(n) will be XML equivalent to the source string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Functions-used-internally","page":"API documentation","title":"Functions used internally","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"CitableTeiReaders.citeNAttr\nCitableTeiReaders.nodefromline","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.citeNAttr","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.citeNAttr","text":"citeNAttr(n, docUrn)\n\n\nConstruct a CitablePassage from an  element with a citable value on @n attribute.\n\n\n\n\n\nciteNAttr(n, docUrn, psg)\n\n\nConstruct a CitablePassage from an  element with citable value on @n attribute.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#CitableTeiReaders.nodefromline","page":"API documentation","title":"CitableTeiReaders.nodefromline","text":"Create a CitablePassage from a string of delimited text.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
